I'll let you off the hook just this once,

252
00:16:54,003 --> 00:16:56,739
but if you come around making
groundless accusations again,

253
00:16:56,739 --> 00:16:58,841
I'll sue you for slander!

254
00:16:58,841 --> 00:17:01,742
Don't think you'll ever find
another job in this industry!

255
00:17:05,648 --> 00:17:08,817
It was better that she hurried up and died?

256
00:17:08,817 --> 00:17:11,718
I won't forgive him. I won't forgive him!

257
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:28,398
Your grievance has been heard.

258
00:17:34,343 --> 00:17:37,870
Ai, I'll leave your under-kimono here.

259
00:17:42,751 --> 00:17:44,844
Thank you, Grandma.

260
00:18:29,631 --> 00:18:33,635
Calling me up in the middle of the night
for a measly dog...

261
00:18:33,635 --> 00:18:36,297
Just you watch, I'll charge you
a fortune for it.

262
00:18:46,982 --> 00:18:47,883
Damn it...

263
00:18:47,883 --> 00:18:51,086
What was someone doing there...

264
00:18:51,086 --> 00:18:52,644
I have a broken bone...

265
00:18:59,061 --> 00:19:01,163
He sure got himself
into a spectacular crash.

266
00:19:01,163 --> 00:19:02,892
Let's move him out.

267
00:19:06,402 --> 00:19:08,199
What're you...

268
00:19:17,246 --> 00:19:18,981
What's this place?

269
00:19:18,981 --> 00:19:20,249
The hospital?

270
00:19:20,249 --> 00:19:22,151
What's going on?

271
00:19:22,151 --> 00:19:23,252
Are you a doctor?

272
00:19:23,252 --> 00:19:25,487
Hey, I've got a broken leg!

273
00:19:25,487 --> 00:19:26,288
Do something about it for me!

274
00:19:26,288 --> 00:19:28,257
Did you see yesterday's game?

275
00:19:28,257 --> 00:19:29,625
Wasn't that an amazing homerun?

276
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:30,893
Who cares about baseball?!

277
00:19:30,893 --> 00:19:33,862
-No, that was because
the pitcher slipped up.
-Hurry up and look at my leg!

278
00:19:33,862 --> 00:19:35,931
A pitcher slip up? Come on!

279
00:19:35,931 --> 00:19:37,733
It was a miscommunication, I'm sure.

280
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:41,103
I mean, it was a straight pitch
smack dab in the middle.

281
00:19:41,103 --> 00:19:43,505
-Hey, you people,
you've got a patient here!
-You were watching, too?

282
00:19:43,505 --> 00:19:46,909
-Quit chitchatting and start treating me!
-I say the credit should go to the batter.

283
00:19:46,909 --> 00:19:47,342
-Quit chitchatting and start treating me!
-He had his elbow
tucked in like this and bam!

284
00:19:47,342 --> 00:19:48,777
-Come on, I told you
-He had his elbow
tucked in like this and bam!

285
00:19:48,777 --> 00:19:50,512
-No one cares about baseball!
-He had his elbow
tucked in like this and bam!

286
00:19:50,512 --> 00:19:52,214
-Hurry up and do something about my leg!
-That was a slip up.

287
00:19:52,214 --> 00:19:53,982
That's right.
Even I could've hit that homerun.

288
00:19:53,982 --> 00:19:56,585
You people, are you listening to me?!

289
00:19:56,585 --> 00:20:00,077
Please, I'm begging you,
do something about this leg!

290
00:20:02,090 --> 00:20:04,726
We will now begin the operation.

291
00:20:04,726 --> 00:20:05,818
What?

292
00:20:08,197 --> 00:20:10,666
What the heck's wrong with him?

293
00:20:10,666 --> 00:20:13,936
The thing is, we can't understand
a word of what the patient's saying.

294
00:20:13,936 --> 00:20:15,137
It's my leg!

295
00:20:15,137 --> 00:20:17,739
-I have a broken bone in my leg!
-I guess we'll start
by cutting in around here.

296
00:20:17,739 --> 00:20:18,797
What?

297
00:20:21,310 --> 00:20:23,312
Where do you people
think you're cutting into?!

298
00:20:23,312 --> 00:20:24,980
That's not the right place! It's my leg!

299
00:20:24,980 --> 00:20:26,448
It's my leg that's injured!

300
00:20:26,448 --> 00:20:28,817
Stop it!

301
00:20:28,817 --> 00:20:32,321
Do you feel like repenting
for what you did now?

302
00:20:32,321 --> 00:20:36,725
To you, animals may be a means
for making money,

303
00:20:36,725 --> 00:20:40,529
but for pet-lovers,
they're a part of the family.

304
00:20:40,529 --> 00:20:43,699
Family?! Don't be ridiculous!

305
00:20:43,699 --> 00:20:46,134
They're no different than I am!

306
00:20:46,134 --> 00:20:48,804
They dress up their animals in weird outfits
and take them to parties!

307
00:20:48,804 --> 00:20:51,240
They use their animals
as a means of showing off!

308
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:54,343
Why am I the only one
that has to be treated like this?!

309
00:20:54,343 --> 00:20:56,445
I haven't done anything wrong!

310
00:20:56,445 --> 00:21:00,115
So he says, Miss.

311
00:21:00,115 --> 00:21:03,285
O pitiful shadow lost in the darkness...

312
00:21:03,285 --> 00:21:06,054
Demeaning and bringing harm to others...

313
00:21:06,054 --> 00:21:08,750
A damned soul, wallowing in sin...

314
00:21:09,658 --> 00:21:12,320
Care to give death a try?

315
00:21:26,975 --> 00:21:28,465
Wh-Where am I?

316
00:21:31,146 --> 00:21:32,581
What is this place?

317
00:21:32,581 --> 00:21:34,276
Where are we going?

318
00:21:37,219 --> 00:21:37,920
Answer me!

319
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:39,721
Doctor, it hurts.

320
00:21:39,721 --> 00:21:41,590
-What?!
-It hurts!

321
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:44,326
-Doctor, it hurts.
-It hurts, Doctor!

322
00:21:44,326 --> 00:21:46,595
-Stop this! Stay away! Stay away from me!
-Doctor!

323
00:21:46,595 --> 00:21:49,364
-Stop this! Stay away! Stay away from me!
-Doctor, it hurts!

324
00:21:49,364 --> 00:21:54,165
I consign this grievance to Hell...

325
00:22:08,050 --> 00:22:09,952
Ms. Sekimoto!

326
00:22:09,952 --> 00:22:13,622
Junko, you came to see me off!

327
00:22:13,622 --> 00:22:15,591
I heard you were leaving the city
and going back home...

328
00:22:15,591 --> 00:22:18,260
I'm sorry. Because of me...

329
00:22:18,260 --> 00:22:20,996
It's okay. I should be the one apologizing.

330
00:22:20,996 --> 00:22:26,702
Besides, I think I can find work
with animals away from the city, too.

331
00:22:26,702 --> 00:22:29,538
The 10:09 Nozomi destined
for Fukuoka will be departing.

332
00:22:29,538 --> 00:22:31,006
-The 10:09 Nozomi destined
for Fukuoka will be departing.
-Well, I have to go.

333
00:22:31,006 --> 00:22:33,542
I'll let you know when I find a job.

334
00:22:33,542 --> 00:22:34,770
Bye.

335
00:22:36,578 --> 00:22:40,716
Father, Mother, Candy...

336
00:22:40,716 --> 00:22:43,385
I'm sad that l can't be with you,

337
00:22:43,385 --> 00:22:45,654
but I'm going to try to
hang in there a little longer.

338
00:22:45,654 --> 00:22:50,523
So, please watch over me from up there.

339
00:22:54,696 --> 00:22:55,197
''Junko Kanno''

